    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul in Charge of the Legation in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-12T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>You may inform President Bogran that the Department regards the executive power
                    as being in his charge in accordance with the terms of the constitution of
                    Honduras. (Article 106)</p>
                <p>Your October 30, 8 p.m. Department believes that it is most advisable that
                    executive power should remain in charge of Bogran until the expiration of the
                    present term.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
